00:17:09.349 --> 00:17:12.880 align:middle line:84%
And so in that sense,
everything is within me,

00:17:12.880 --> 00:17:15.130 align:middle line:84%
because it's within
my experience.

00:17:15.130 --> 00:17:17.319 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, Einstein, when
he developed his theory

00:17:17.319 --> 00:17:21.550 align:middle line:84%
of relativity, he engaged in the
thought experiment of imagining

00:17:21.550 --> 00:17:25.450 align:middle line:84%
what it would be like
to travel on a photon.

00:17:25.450 --> 00:17:28.600 align:middle line:84%
And if a photon could
speak, wouldn't a photon

00:17:28.600 --> 00:17:31.210 align:middle line:84%
say something to the effect
that I am the universe,

00:17:31.210 --> 00:17:35.310 align:middle line:84%
meaning the physical universe
is all contained within?

00:17:35.310 --> 00:17:37.240 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm not sure.

00:17:37.240 --> 00:17:39.260 align:middle line:84%
A photon wouldn't
have time to speak.

00:17:39.260 --> 00:17:41.750 align:middle line:84%
A photon doesn't exist
in space and time.

00:17:41.750 --> 00:17:43.330 align:middle line:90%
It is a moment.

00:17:43.330 --> 00:17:47.640 align:middle line:90%
It is just a zero point of time.

00:17:47.640 --> 00:17:49.520 align:middle line:84%
Time exists outside
of the photon.

00:17:49.520 --> 00:17:52.670 align:middle line:84%
But for that photon, it
doesn't actually exist in time.

00:17:52.670 --> 00:17:56.980 align:middle line:84%
It is just a moment,
a zero moment.

00:17:56.980 --> 00:18:00.560 align:middle line:84%
>> If time exists
outside of the photon,

00:18:00.560 --> 00:18:02.980 align:middle line:84%
then you're suggesting
that there are two realms,

00:18:02.980 --> 00:18:05.020 align:middle line:84%
a realm of time and
a realm of no time.

00:18:05.020 --> 00:18:06.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly, yes.

00:18:06.710 --> 00:18:08.900 align:middle line:84%
And that's true of
consciousness as well.

00:18:08.900 --> 00:18:10.480 align:middle line:84%
When you go deep
into meditation,

00:18:10.480 --> 00:18:13.690 align:middle line:84%
you reach that timeless state,
which I think many people have

00:18:13.690 --> 00:18:17.350 align:middle line:84%
experienced, where you
don't-- time disappears.

00:18:17.350 --> 00:18:20.390 align:middle line:84%
And you can be there for
10 minutes, 10 hours.

00:18:20.390 --> 00:18:21.190 align:middle line:90%
You don't know.

00:18:21.190 --> 00:18:23.440 align:middle line:84%
It's just you have that
experience of timelessness.

00:18:23.440 --> 00:18:26.440 align:middle line:84%
And yet in our daily
world, consciousness

00:18:26.440 --> 00:18:28.420 align:middle line:84%
takes on clearly
the forms of time.

00:18:28.420 --> 00:18:31.580 align:middle line:84%
We are aware very much now
of the passing of time.

00:18:31.580 --> 00:18:34.900 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, there's something as
a parapsychologist that really

00:18:34.900 --> 00:18:36.700 align:middle line:84%
interests me, which
is precognition,

00:18:36.700 --> 00:18:40.570 align:middle line:84%
the capacity of our
consciousness to know things

00:18:40.570 --> 00:18:43.210 align:middle line:84%
that have not yet happened,
that would seem to be physically

00:18:43.210 --> 00:18:44.810 align:middle line:90%
impossible to know.

00:18:44.810 --> 00:18:45.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:18:45.610 --> 00:18:49.240 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's a whole other
question and how that happens,

00:18:49.240 --> 00:18:51.658 align:middle line:84%
when it happens, if it does
happen, which cases are true.

00:18:51.658 --> 00:18:53.200 align:middle line:84%
There are so many
questions about it.

00:18:53.200 --> 00:18:56.600 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I will attest
that it does happen.

00:18:56.600 --> 00:18:57.850 align:middle line:90%
I've seen it happen.

00:18:57.850 --> 00:19:01.090 align:middle line:84%
It's been well documented in
hundreds of laboratory studies.

00:19:01.090 --> 00:19:06.100 align:middle line:84%
And it would seem to me that
your description here of light

00:19:06.100 --> 00:19:10.900 align:middle line:84%
would provide, not a
mechanism, but a foundation

00:19:10.900 --> 00:19:15.820 align:middle line:84%
within which precognition
can seem to be more normal.

00:19:15.820 --> 00:19:19.300 align:middle line:84%
>> It certainly shows that it's
not so far out as one would

00:19:19.300 --> 00:19:20.260 align:middle line:90%
initially expect.

00:19:20.260 --> 00:19:23.350 align:middle line:84%
I don't think it offers a
simple explanation for it.

00:19:23.350 --> 00:19:26.520 align:middle line:84%
But I think we get caught
up sometimes in the belief

00:19:26.520 --> 00:19:29.880 align:middle line:84%
that our current state
of knowledge is the end,

00:19:29.880 --> 00:19:31.777 align:middle line:84%
and there are so many
things we don't know.

00:19:31.777 --> 00:19:34.360 align:middle line:84%
And we just have to go back 100
years ago to look at the world

00:19:34.360 --> 00:19:35.200 align:middle line:90%
view of people then.

00:19:35.200 --> 00:19:37.030 align:middle line:90%
Compare that to today.

00:19:37.030 --> 00:19:40.210 align:middle line:84%
Or go back 2,000 years ago
to what the Greeks understood

00:19:40.210 --> 00:19:43.420 align:middle line:84%
about the world and
realize they thought

00:19:43.420 --> 00:19:44.890 align:middle line:90%
they had it all sorted out.

00:19:44.890 --> 00:19:47.680 align:middle line:84%
And for us to think we know
how the world works is I

00:19:47.680 --> 00:19:49.210 align:middle line:90%
think the grossest arrogance.

00:19:49.210 --> 00:19:52.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think if I were to
try and provide a mechanism

00:19:52.660 --> 00:19:56.170 align:middle line:84%
for you as to how precognition
could possibly occur,

00:19:56.170 --> 00:19:59.380 align:middle line:90%
that would be very arrogant.

00:19:59.380 --> 00:20:01.510 align:middle line:84%
I don't know that we'll
ever be able to do that.

00:20:01.510 --> 00:20:03.168 align:middle line:84%
>> It may not even
involve mechanisms.

00:20:03.168 --> 00:20:04.210 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, that's my point.

00:20:04.210 --> 00:20:05.050 align:middle line:84%
>> We're caught
in a mechanistic--

00:20:05.050 --> 00:20:05.350 align:middle line:90%
>> You're right.

00:20:05.350 --> 00:20:06.150 align:middle line:90%
--mode of thinking.

00:20:06.150 --> 00:20:08.530 align:middle line:84%
>> The very need for a mechanism
is part of the problem.

00:20:08.530 --> 00:20:11.170 align:middle line:84%
But to suggest, as I
think you have suggested,

00:20:11.170 --> 00:20:14.470 align:middle line:84%
that all is already contained
within consciousness,

00:20:14.470 --> 00:20:17.230 align:middle line:84%
that consciousness partakes
of a realm which is completely

00:20:17.230 --> 00:20:22.030 align:middle line:84%
outside of time, would suggest
to me it could have access,

00:20:22.030 --> 00:20:25.060 align:middle line:90%
therefore, to any point in time.

00:20:25.060 --> 00:20:28.090 align:middle line:84%
And perhaps it's just biological
conditioning that keeps it

00:20:28.090 --> 00:20:29.270 align:middle line:90%
from happening more often.

00:20:29.270 --> 00:20:30.070 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:20:30.070 --> 00:20:32.070 align:middle line:84%
What it suggests to me
as our current world view

00:20:32.070 --> 00:20:35.860 align:middle line:84%
is so small compared to the
immensity of what is obviously

00:20:35.860 --> 00:20:37.150 align:middle line:90%
going on in the universe.

00:20:37.150 --> 00:20:40.780 align:middle line:84%
And the current world
view cannot understand it,

00:20:40.780 --> 00:20:42.190 align:middle line:90%
cannot encompass it.

00:20:42.190 --> 00:20:44.560 align:middle line:84%
Try as we may, we
just get-- our minds,

00:20:44.560 --> 00:20:46.128 align:middle line:84%
like I'm sure many
viewers' minds are

00:20:46.128 --> 00:20:47.170 align:middle line:90%
stretching at the moment.

00:20:47.170 --> 00:20:50.023 align:middle line:84%
All that happens is
our minds go, what?

00:20:50.023 --> 00:20:51.440 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, we're
limited, of course,

00:20:51.440 --> 00:20:52.910 align:middle line:90%
by our cultural conditioning.

00:20:52.910 --> 00:20:55.280 align:middle line:84%
I think we're also limited
by our biological--

00:20:55.280 --> 00:20:56.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly--

00:20:56.080 --> 00:20:56.880 align:middle line:90%
--conditioning.

00:20:56.880 --> 00:20:59.680 align:middle line:84%
>> --because we're sitting here
functioning within physical

00:20:59.680 --> 00:21:02.050 align:middle line:84%
organisms which don't move
at the speed of light,

00:21:02.050 --> 00:21:04.423 align:middle line:84%
and we have all
that conditioning.

00:21:04.423 --> 00:21:07.090 align:middle line:84%
So I think we are forced to just
see the world through this very

00:21:07.090 --> 00:21:08.710 align:middle line:90%
narrow perspective.

00:21:08.710 --> 00:21:11.410 align:middle line:84%
>> It's probably fair to
assume that under favorable

00:21:11.410 --> 00:21:15.130 align:middle line:84%
conditions, the human race
will evolve to a point where

00:21:15.130 --> 00:21:18.660 align:middle line:84%
consciousness will transcend
both cultural and biological

00:21:18.660 --> 00:21:19.780 align:middle line:90%
conditioning.

00:21:19.780 --> 00:21:21.947 align:middle line:84%
>> This is why I think the
mystics are so important,

00:21:21.947 --> 00:21:24.650 align:middle line:84%
the great saints and yogis and
sages which have been dotted

00:21:24.650 --> 00:21:25.450 align:middle line:90%
through time.

00:21:25.450 --> 00:21:29.920 align:middle line:84%
I think they are the heralds of
what is to come for humanity.

00:21:29.920 --> 00:21:31.750 align:middle line:84%
They are just little
individuals who

00:21:31.750 --> 00:21:34.540 align:middle line:84%
have discovered the true
nature of consciousness.

00:21:34.540 --> 00:21:36.970 align:middle line:84%
When I say little, I mean
just a few individuals.

00:21:36.970 --> 00:21:40.940 align:middle line:84%
And I think where we are going
is that sort of experience

00:21:40.940 --> 00:21:42.440 align:middle line:90%
becoming the norm.

00:21:42.440 --> 00:21:45.650 align:middle line:84%
That I think is our evolutionary
potential as a species.

00:21:45.650 --> 00:21:49.580 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, those great spiritual
geniuses and heroes and saints

00:21:49.580 --> 00:21:51.000 align:middle line:90%
can serve as role models and--

00:21:51.000 --> 00:21:51.800 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:21:51.800 --> 00:21:52.600 align:middle line:90%
>> --templates.

00:21:52.600 --> 00:21:55.520 align:middle line:84%
And their experience
can probably

00:21:55.520 --> 00:21:57.480 align:middle line:84%
become more accessible
to more people.

00:21:57.480 --> 00:21:58.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:21:58.280 --> 00:21:59.630 align:middle line:84%
I think that's what
is happening today.

00:21:59.630 --> 00:22:00.572 align:middle line:90%
More and more people--

00:22:00.572 --> 00:22:03.030 align:middle line:84%
I think for the first time ever
in the history of humanity,

00:22:03.030 --> 00:22:05.210 align:middle line:84%
you have millions and
millions of people

00:22:05.210 --> 00:22:06.500 align:middle line:90%
wanting to explore this.

00:22:06.500 --> 00:22:08.530 align:middle line:84%
They are getting on with
their life and work,

00:22:08.530 --> 00:22:11.300 align:middle line:84%
but at the same time they're
studying meditation or yoga

00:22:11.300 --> 00:22:14.030 align:middle line:84%
or working on themselves
in one way or another.

00:22:14.030 --> 00:22:16.610 align:middle line:84%
And they're not reaching at
the moment such depths as many

00:22:16.610 --> 00:22:17.590 align:middle line:84%
of the great
mystics, but there's

00:22:17.590 --> 00:22:20.020 align:middle line:84%
this movement in that direction,
this groundswell which

00:22:20.020 --> 00:22:20.820 align:middle line:90%
is happening.

00:22:20.820 --> 00:22:23.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, your work is very
inspiring in that regard,

00:22:23.270 --> 00:22:27.980 align:middle line:84%
Peter, because you're showing
that that path towards a higher

00:22:27.980 --> 00:22:30.710 align:middle line:84%
consciousness, towards an
awakening can occur through

00:22:30.710 --> 00:22:32.810 align:middle line:84%
meditation, can occur
through science,

00:22:32.810 --> 00:22:35.690 align:middle line:84%
can occur through a more
enlightened business practice.

00:22:35.690 --> 00:22:36.620 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:22:36.620 --> 00:22:38.690 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's all coming
together at this time

00:22:38.690 --> 00:22:40.310 align:middle line:84%
and all moving in
the same direction.

00:22:40.310 --> 00:22:43.530 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, Peter Russell, I regard
you as a role model in that

00:22:43.530 --> 00:22:44.330 align:middle line:90%
regard.

00:22:44.330 --> 00:22:47.900 align:middle line:84%
You're very clear and
articulate about issues that are

00:22:47.900 --> 00:22:49.645 align:middle line:90%
hard for most people to grasp.

00:22:49.645 --> 00:22:51.020 align:middle line:84%
Thanks so much
for being with me.

00:22:51.020 --> 00:22:51.820 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:22:51.820 --> 00:22:53.930 align:middle line:90%
>> It's been a pleasure.

